It would be better to go with the following change below so that it follows our header include rules. I have verified this on my local Windows machine. The basic.h file ultimately includes Windows.h, and sets all the right defines.

```
+#include "mongo/platform/basic.h"
+
 #ifdef _WIN32
+#include <mmsystem.h>
 #include <crtdbg.h>
 #include <stdlib.h>
 #include <stdio.h>
 #endif

 #include "mongo/base/init.h"
 #include "mongo/util/log.h"
 #include "mongo/util/stacktrace.h"
```

