review_comments.body:
Instead of an erase and then a re-insert here, could you do the following instead?

``` cpp
invariant(!nary->vpOperand.empty());
vpOperand[i] = std::move(nary->vpOperand[0]);
vpOperand.insert(vpOperand.begin() + i, nary->vpOperand.begin() + 1, nary->vpOperand.end());
```

It would save two shifts of the array from erasing and then re-inserting.

